elements.label: Section-header
elements.text: Students around the country are noticing La Salle.

elements.label: Section-header
elements.text: Some of them have questions only you can answer.

elements.label: Text
elements.text: Alumni are the most credible source of information for many prospective students and their parents. That’s why we're inviting you to become part of the La Salle Explorer Alumni Recruiting Network (L.E.A.R.N.). There are several ways you can share your La Salle experiences with students and parents:

elements.label: List-item
elements.text: e Represent the university at college nights and receptions in your area.

elements.label: List-item
elements.text: e Call students who are interested in La Salle.

elements.label: List-item
elements.text: e Write a letter on company stationery about your work experience and your La Salle education.

elements.label: List-item
elements.text: ¢ Visit high schools to discuss your profession and your preparation at La Salle.

elements.label: Text
elements.text: If you are interested in helping the university recruit tomorrow’s graduates, please call Maryhelen Driscoll, associate director of admissions, at 215/951-1500. Or return the coupon below.

elements.label: Text
elements.text: I'd like to play a role in recruiting students to La Salle.

elements.label: Text
elements.text: oe . . Mail to: Office of Admissions La Salle University Philadelphia, PA 19141-1199

elements.label: Text
elements.text: LA SALLE EXPLORER ALUMNI RECRUITING NETWORK

elements.label: Page-footer
elements.text: La Salle appears in many of the nation's leading guidebooks.
